Benue State Police Command has confirmed the arrest of Sergeant James Aondona for alleged culpable homicide in Katsina-Ala Local Government Area. Police spokesperson, Sewuese Anene said on June 26 at about 1230hrs, the suspect was posted to an observation point at Ngibo, Katsina-Ala, adding that around the location, Aondona engaged in an altercation which led to the death of Aondohemba Terkula. The body of the deceased has been deposited at the General Hospital in Kastina-Ala LGA. Commissioner of Police, Wale Abass condemned the unprofessional conduct of the officer and assured that the suspect would be prosecuted to ensure justice is served.